title.narrative: Strengthening the Supportive Environment and Scaling up Prevention, Treatment and Care to Contain the HIV Epidemic in the Republic of Tajikistan

description.narrative: Tajikistan - HIV - United Nations Development Programme - UNDP Tajikistan. This program has the following goals: To achieve universal access to HIV services; prevention, care, treatment and support that enables people with HIV to live a fulfilling life. The objectives of this program are: Programme management: capacity development of MoHSPP and support of procurement and supply management. Health System Strengthening by integration of health service delivery and optimisation of human resources. Ensure quality care and treatment for the people living with HIV/AIDS and TB. Strengthened supportive environment to improve access to services for Key Population. Ensure high quality and coverage of prevention services for key populations (PWID, SW, MSM, prisoners, including their partners)
